OL,6,FHead of Strategy at Panmure Liberum,
OL,7,FJoachim Klement, said it could be
OL,8,Fworse than the oil and gas shock seen
OL,9,Fin 2022 after Russia's invasion of
OL,10,FUkraine and the subsequent sanctions
OL,11,Fagainst Russian oil and gas exports.
OL,13,FMr Klement said: "If the Straits of
OL,14,FHormuz is shut, we expect a major
OL,15,Fstagflationary shock similar to 2022.
OL,17,F"In this case, a 10% to 20% correction
OL,18,Fseems likely and we could see a new
OL,19,Fbear market if the trade war escalates
OL,20,Fagain in early July."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
