OL,6,FBut he said if the Strait of Hormuz is
OL,7,Fdisrupted but not closed, "the
OL,8,Finflation shock will be significant,
OL,9,Fbut not enough to derail markets and
OL,10,Fthe economies of the US, the UK and
OL,11,FEurozone for too long".
OL,13,F"In this scenario, we expect an
OL,14,Finitial correction of stock markets of
OL,15,F5% to 10%.
OL,17,F"Whether this correction lasts longer
OL,18,Fand becomes deeper depends very much
OL,19,Fon how the trade war unfolds in the
OL,20,Fnext couple of weeks."
